1
00:00:01,200 --> 00:00:07,800
One room. One clear next step.

2
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:15,500
First, understand the room before you enter.

3
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:24,000
Ask the event question you actually have. NameTags keeps the context and makes the answer useful.

4
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:31,200
Research stays private. You decide what gets shared next.

5
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:40,500
Second, choose the version of you this room meets.

6
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:47,500
The scanner preview makes the public and private boundary clear before anyone scans.

7
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:55,500
Then hold up one QR pass instead of hunting for the right profile or contact app.

8
00:00:56,000 --> 00:01:01,500
The other person sees only Diego's selected public card and links.

9
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:10,500
Third, follow through while the conversation is still fresh.

10
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:18,500
Keep who you met, what you promised, and an editable AI draft in one place.

11
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:24,500
AI does the organizing. You still decide what gets sent.

12
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:31,000
The goal is not more contacts. It is one useful next step.

13
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:39,000
Understand the room. Share the right card. Follow through.

14
00:01:39,500 --> 00:01:40,000
NameTags. Networking, without the pressure.
